CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 4, 1960, pg.23 reads: "Insurance Winners - The North Carolina Mutual Life Insurance Company won the annual trophy for top sales in competition with the American Woodmen, Provident Home Industrial and Supreme Liberty Life. The trophy rotates annually to the winner, but it can be won permanently by the company first to win it three times.  Left to right: Maude Y. Hawkins, staff manager; Offerell Johnson, president; U.E. Finley, chairman of Pittsburgh's National Insurance Week, while John D. Lewis Sr., retired manager, and Manager Harry H. Carter look on. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of North Carolina Mutual Life Insurance winners, from left: Maude Y. Hawkins, Offerell Johnson, U.E. Finley, chairman of Pittsburgh's National Insurance Week; John D. Lewis Sr., and Harry H. Carter,  posed in Loendi Club
